tbh-meter — https://github.com/mad-labs-org/tbh-meter
================================================================================

The built-in live meter (live DPS / gold / EXP tracking, the read-only Windows
memory sensor, the IL2CPP object layouts, the game offset table, and the run
lifecycle model) is a Rust derivative work of `mad-labs-org/tbh-meter`, whose
original implementation is a Python reader (`tbh-reader.exe`) plus an Electron
overlay. The functionality has been reimplemented natively in Rust in:

  - src-tauri/src/memory.rs   (process attach + read primitives + IL2CPP layouts)
  - src-tauri/src/meter.rs    (sampling loop, metrics, run tracking)
  - data/meter-offsets.json   (IL2CPP + game offsets, enums, calibration seed)

